AB  - We obtain the Information Matrix test for finite Gaussian mixtures exploiting the EM principle, which implies the moments tested are the expectation given the data of the moments one would assess if one knew the latent component each observation belongs to. Simulations indicate analytical expressions for the asymptotic covariance matrix of those moments adjusted for sampling variability in parameter estimators provide reliable finite sample sizes and good power against various alternatives, especially combined with the parametric bootstrap. We apply the test to the univariate distribution of per capita income across countries and its joint distribution with per capita CO2 emissions.
